title: Obesity
summary: Obesity is defined as having a body mass index (BMI) of 30 or more.
body: Obesity has been shown to be associated with diabetes, heart disease, lung disease, arhtritis, and shortened life span.
personalizedBody: A normal BMI is between 18.5 and 24.9.  To have a normal BMI, you would have to get down to @{Math.round(Height * Height * 24.9)} kg (@{Math.round(Height * Height * 54.78)} lb).

title: Overweight
summary: Overweight is defined as having a body mass index (BMI) of 25 to 29.9.
body: Being overweight has been shown to be associated with diabetes, heart disease, and shortened life expectancy.
personalizedBody: A normal BMI is between 18.5 and 24.9.  To have a normal BMI, you would have to get down to @{Math.round(Height * Height * 24.9)} kg (@{Math.round(Height * Height * 54.78)} lb).
